parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dual gas tank system can cause fuel leaks, overflow, and pressure buildup, leading to potential fire hazards and accidents.
symptoms: siphoning of fuel from one tank to another.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to potential fire hazards and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leak from the intake manifold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the thermostat can cause the engine to overheat, leading to potential engine damage, breakdown, or even engine failure, which can result in costly repairs or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine temperature gauge rises above normal
the radiator fan fails to turn on
the engine makes unusual noises or produces excessive heat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankcase breathing system can cause smoke to enter the engine, leading to spontaneous combustion or runaway engine, which can result in engine damage, breakdown, or even accidents.

The failure of the exhaust manifold can cause exhaust fumes and odors to enter the vehicle's cabin, which can lead to health risks for occupants and potentially cause accidents due to driver distraction or discomfort.
symptoms: excessive noise from the exhaust system
exhaust fumes or odors entering the vehicle's cabin

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate seat belt retention can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly secured.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to hold securely during an accident
the seat belt does not retract properly
the seat belt hangs out when getting out of the vehicle
the seat belt gets caught in the door when entering the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to blown fuses, charging system failures, and potentially, electrical fires, which can result in accidents, property damage, and personal injury.
symptoms: failure of the charging system to properly charge batteries

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical fire in the steering column can spread to other areas of the vehicle, causing property damage, personal injury, and potentially, accidents.
symptoms: Visible signs of fire or smoke emanating from the steering column

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty speedometer head can cause inaccurate speed readings, which can lead to unsafe driving practices, such as speeding or failure to adjust to road conditions.
A transfer case oil leak can cause the transfer case to overheat, leading to premature wear and failure, which can result in loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the transfer case
unusual noises or vibrations from the transfer case

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty universal joint can cause vibrations that can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and premature wear on other components.
symptoms: Unusual noises or vibrations from the left/rear axle
clunking or grinding sounds when accelerating or decelerating
difficulty steering or maintaining vehicle direction.
